		<p>I&#8217;m a lawyer and here&#8217;s the scoop.  We never create a contract out of whole cloth.  We just cut and paste old contracts, find forms from treatises, or pull out a contract from a previous transaction that closely resembles the current transaction.  It&#8217;s rarely tailored.  It&#8217;s like a suit bought from JC Penny&#8217;s.  It does the trick, but is not made for the man.  Your contract is much better than any contract a lawyer could draft.</p>


